<subSubSection id="C330B6812DEBE32682648ADDC3142305" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5F85B3D91F7D9B856C0A430793FD8AD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2AF1EB2D16A88F3F847FA667D5A5598A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Antenna orange ventrally, oval, longer than wide. Costal cell hyaline, bare basally. Alula bare medially. Pro- and mesofemur yellow. Metafemur orange on basal 1/5 and apical 3/5. Probasitarsomere, meso- and metabasitarsomere I-II yellow. Second tergum with a broad macula reaching apical 1/3. Third tergum with a broad macula, short in fourth. Sternite fourth to fifth black pilose. 
<taxonomicName id="279422E09F11F455D105946BFD834B8C" authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia puntarena" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis id="93D3B5C05F96793E28BA3760CFE58745" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="DF4B461CF4F4AE82B984E1984BE73512" authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia talamanca" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis id="25BC23FE4D04023F22DBFEB6894348E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but in 
<taxonomicName id="609B170F3AACA2F95B93ADA7D2E03CC9" genus="A." lsidName="A. talamanca" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis id="4131070DB5D659862E829AC5EB863EAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A. talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. the antenna is brown; alula and costal cell are extensively microtrichose; femur is extensively brown; the second tergum has a pair of small maculae on basal 1/5 (see 'diagnostic 
<normalizedToken id="C7B214CA95D69A0BBE67A54CBB01C844" originalValue="features’">features'</normalizedToken>
under each species or key).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BDEB5A6FB41C90ABE349114CFC07D33C" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="6BAFC96C206D305B2C1641C92CFB42AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="02533CA635D1D90EE14C134F2A39A36A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Costa Rica, department of Puntarenas, Coto Brus municipality, Sendero entre 
<normalizedToken id="552C32B262B85368BFFE01748B619D3B" originalValue="Estación">Estacion</normalizedToken>
Tres Colinas y Laguna Seca, 
<geoCoordinate id="667802471DC3A937015305BFD893EA3E" degrees="9" direction="north" minutes="1.279" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="9.021317">9°1.279'N</geoCoordinate>
, 82°, 50.337'E, 2100-2550 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87D98108464481A69A08CBE1F9C12623" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="6E4A5FEB26D36D1E9A813871C0A07A28" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D676419E45BDED109AB7DD593EE1CF21" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="14B4E892AA9F4E2525BA7F09561C3DCF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Male. Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3299AC1390207C117DF13BFB65040B3A" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6A, C</figureCitation>
). Black, covered with white pollinosity, ocellar triangle, and a large triangular macula on the front, brown pilose, pile on front black, on gena and face white pilose, on ocellar triangle black pilose, on the occiput white except for the dorsal pile, which are black, frontal triangle golden metallic. Antennae brown, orange-red ventrally, oval, longer than wide pedicel and the lower basal corner of basoflagellomere, ratio 1.0:1.1:2.9, arista orange, dark brown toward the tip. 
<emphasis id="4C893F80372A7B166B2ED1A252FC33A8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ED8FDC37472D66054E5C0148BC8CFD35" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6C</figureCitation>
). Black, scutum shining, with iridescent to opaque reflections, with two median brownish pollinose vittae on anterior half. 
<emphasis id="F8684A9E23F86F7EBF51A65B67EFFAD9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D1F3A31068F2BB6732AAF00D241B6308" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6C</figureCitation>
). Slightly smoky, the stigma brownish, membrane microtrichose, except for extensive bare areas on basal half (cells, sc, r1, dm and bm); costal cell hyaline, bare on basal 1/2; marginal maculae restricted to surrounding areas of veins R1, R4+5 and M1 apically; tegula black pilose, basicosta yellow pilose, alula bare medially, calypter whitish, border whitish, fringe yellow, plumula yellow, halter yellow, knob white. 
<emphasis id="0E96438B28B7C3EE46B8D84457E71F4C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D93B635FA77063835FF4623FD24F8479" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6C</figureCitation>
). Yellow, pro- and mesofemur yellow; metafemur brown, except orange on basal 1/5 and apical 1/5; pro and mesotibia orange, metatibia extensively brown, only orange brownish on basal 2/3; probasitarsomere, meso- and metabasitarsomere I-II yellow, the pile yellow, black on the metatibia and above on the tarsi. 
<emphasis id="A7EEE24D055F8B9E2E766376DFE73561" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="97546CBAB67726498F63999044F34C24" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6B</figureCitation>
). Elongate, black, the first tergum shining black, orange laterally, the second tergum with a broad macula reaching apical 1/3 laterally; third tergum with a broad triangular macula, which is short in the fourth tergum; fourth and fifth sterna black pilose. Pile orange on the sides basally, as well as in the maculae, black down the middle and on the terga apex. Male genitalia as Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F369D306B3069EB1FE5698737ED38884" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male genitalia: A whole genitalia including epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view B epandrium, dorsal view C hypandrium, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402761" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">7</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09557E1904B313457431ABD39A9EEBE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="5B393FABB26B422021E01FC20228DDAA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Female.</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B44558F714F0D6BDEEF7841BDBCDAD93" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Argentinomyia puntarena sp. nov., male (InBio CRI 000311623): A head, frontal, male B dorsal view C lateral view. Female (InBio CRI 002427774): D head, frontal view E dorsal view F lateral view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402760" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">6D-F</figureCitation>
). Similar to male except for normal sexual dimorphism. Frons with pollinose transversal maculae below. Abdominal maculae are comparatively shorter than in the male and indistinguishable in the fourth tergum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="687C76BF4D2FDE48053666D6FCB30AB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="40F48DEAEC8DCDEFFB59B1A1F86ED15C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Length</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="327BF812DEC8B51D62C74F378C2F639B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">N</emphasis>
= 4). Body 12.4-12.6 mm; wing 11.3-11.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="01E8EBCA4C2BEB7694FFFD707EDF9A2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="668770847A24C8FE9ED338ED12E53EC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10633A4FA787BCD010E1FFD75163E9C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="ED722945118F220DA7F02E94DF050D09" genus="A." lsidName="puntarena" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis id="35616DD2810165324DC3C131CA3610DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a noun in apposition and refers to the province where the type series was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D41C9D2D91A6889F30061CD1A4F999C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="774F58E9F2453680C09FC240A9A51C04" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29A0C27B9723BA4C4035E5DAFD667EC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="B8C390437FF991463D65FBA180AEA78B" authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia puntarena" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis id="87FF9CA0982FA5E8B2E3EB622050F522" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (
<emphasis id="1D9E4E5E6EFCD72A4D0723E3EC9B55E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">N</emphasis>
= 5) is distributed through the west slope of the 
<taxonomicName id="441E9B9CB31D2E9B65991FA9512E85FA" genus="Talamanca" lsidName="Talamanca" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="genus">Talamanca</taxonomicName>
Cordillera in Costa Rica (Puntarenas, San 
<normalizedToken id="4D8B94FCA39611356AB2D8CC24BEABD4" originalValue="José">Jose</normalizedToken>
) at an elevation between 1000 to 2550 m. a.s.l., in the province of 
<normalizedToken id="C03AE0B2E8949B1F995CC277F0823419" originalValue="Puntarena-Chiriquí">Puntarena-Chiriqui</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4682621D0F67EC4D09C7AE2397FA24C0" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Biogeographical distribution of Argentinomyia huitepecensis sp. nov. (green), A. talamanca sp. nov. (red) and A. puntarenas sp. nov. (blue)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.37666.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402770" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">16</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E30F0500D6CB7A2650D4F127907AB84B" authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia puntarena" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis id="9D108A5A3797FFAD08FDB802B42F4FD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. occurs in sympatry with 
<taxonomicName id="FC90806C8E6121E72B75C2CC5111CF07" genus="A." lsidName="A. talamanca" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis id="F52C2E5A0F848241B2170150353CA738" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A. talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in the 
<normalizedToken id="06DB2733799886C29552DE5245CD21F6" originalValue="Puntarena-Chiriquí">Puntarena-Chiriqui</normalizedToken>
province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1563714FDAD79F23D311F12164D89CC8" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="type material">
