<paragraph id="182926D76C89966E9B70FF29A7EF93B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F551B80B6B877614911B13445E8B4B9D" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="1E1B3CD7B6387A4244FDE90C7687E445" authorityName="Montoya" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia puntarena" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntarena">
<emphasis id="A05F730A6D054454717FA2D391E8C938" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia puntarena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="7601CED8AE1A148896B4720A48C752A9" authorityName="Thompson" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Argentinomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argentinomyia talamanca" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talamanca">
<emphasis id="59880A90255C0941C521516372828B32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Argentinomyia talamanca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be confused or mistakenly identified as 
<taxonomicName id="72985CFA2B23165DBD5FE28ECD622020" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthandrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xanthandrus mexicanus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="971444180E47AF206FD2C78C6010097C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Xanthandrus mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Curran, 1930 due to the superficial similarity of these species. However, 
<taxonomicName id="88174267E721E347CC16997737DAEED2" genus="X." lsidName="X. mexicanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="A83BCFACCB48CE7E5EA42A37ADD31E74" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">X. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the presence of the antennal cavity broadly confluent (synapomorphy for 
<taxonomicName id="F1EF45870013BF95385680F160480ADD" authorityName="Verrall" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthandrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xanthandrus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="101355C294917A8EFEC8ADFB17017E3A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Xanthandrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the central portion of epistoma moderately prominent; the face entirely white pollinose and pilose; the pleura black with white pollinosity; metaepisternum with some fine subappressed long pile (distinctive of 
<taxonomicName id="D4D04EE5F9D3AD22066FF7F5A433A0D3" authorityName="Verrall" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthandrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xanthandrus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9EEF70A0A978C8488B8400638460A5CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Xanthandrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the abdomen oval, wide and flat, opaque, with yellow-orange triangular maculae on second to the fourth tergum, and the male genitalia with surstylus elongated, apically widened (
<bibRefCitation id="35D625FF6D4BD6440ABAD40C8DDD31CA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/S0085-56262003000200002" author="Borges, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Revista Brasileira de Entomologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="155 - 167" refId="B2" refString="Borges, ZM, Pamplona, DM, 2003. Revision of the Neotropical Xanthandrus Verral (Diptera, Syrphidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 47: 155 - 167, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1590/S0085-56262003000200002" title="Revision of the Neotropical Xanthandrus Verral (Diptera, Syrphidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/S0085-56262003000200002" volume="47" year="2003">Borges and Pamplona 2003</bibRefCitation>
:162, figs 33-37).
</paragraph>
